.TH GIT-PR-RESTACK 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-restack \- rebase one GitHub pull request branch onto a base
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-restack
.RI [ options ]
.I number|url|branch
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-restack
rebases one open pull request head branch onto a base branch and pushes with
.BR \-\-force\-with\-lease .
By default, the base is the pull request's current base branch.
.PP
When a new base is given and the push succeeds, the command updates the GitHub
pull request base.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-base " " \fIbranch\fR
Rebase onto this branch and update the pull request base.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-push
Rebase locally without pushing or editing the pull request base.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Print actions without changing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Pull request branch was restacked.
.TP
.B 1
Restack failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-stack (1),
.BR git-pr-land-stack (1)
